Members of Congress and various state officials from the Republican party expressed their support and admiration for President Trump's State of the Union address. They praised his accomplishments in areas such as the economy, job creation, national security, and trade deals. They also highlighted his optimism and vision for the future of America. Cabinet officials, including Secretary of State Mike Pompeo and Secretary of the Treasury Steve Mnuchin, commended President Trump's leadership and his commitment to the American people. Media commentators and policy advocates, such as Fox News contributor Ari Fleischer and Forbes Media Chairman Steve Forbes, also had positive reactions to the speech, calling it powerful and moving.